  "prompt": "I work as deputy manager in a nationalised bank. I wank to work as an investment banker. I am a graduate. What courses should I do?",
  "response": "To transition from a nationalized bank to investment banking, consider the following courses and steps:\n\n1. Professional Certifications:\n- Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA)\n- Financial Risk Manager (FRM)\n- Investment Banking Certification from NISM\n- Certified Investment Banking Professional (CIBP)\n\n2. Postgraduate Courses:\n- MBA in Finance\n- MBA in Investment Banking\n- Postgraduate Diploma in Investment Banking\n- Master of Finance (MFin)\n\n3. Online Courses:\n- Investment Banking courses from platforms like Coursera, edX\n- Wall Street Prep\n- Corporate Finance Institute (CFI) courses\n\n4. Skill Development:\n- Financial Modeling\n- Valuation techniques\n- Advanced Excel skills\n- Understanding of M&A, IPOs, capital markets\n\n5. Networking:\n- Join professional networks like LinkedIn\n- Attend financial conferences\n- Connect with investment banking professionals\n\n6. Additional Recommendations:\n- Gain knowledge of financial markets\n- Develop strong analytical and communication skills\n- Consider internships or part-time opportunities in investment banking\n- Stay updated with financial news and trends\n\nChoose courses based on your budget, time availability, and specific career goals.",
